Millville first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Millville had a population of 724. The population density was {{convert|90.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Millville was 651 (89.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 8 (1.1%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 5 (0.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.1%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 3 (0.4%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 56 (7.7%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 35 persons (4.8%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Millville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0647724 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 287 households, out of which 72 (25.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 189 (65.9%) were married-couple households, 12 (4.2%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 48 (16.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 38 (13.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 64 households (22.3%) were one person, and 40 (13.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.52.<ref name=DP1/> There were 210 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (73.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Millville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0647724 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 150 people (20.7%) under the age of 18, 49 people (6.8%) aged 18 to 24, 114 people (15.7%) aged 25 to 44, 209 people (28.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 202 people (27.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 51.2{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 79.2 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 311 housing units at an average density of {{convert|38.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 287 (92.3%) were occupied. Of these, 253 (88.2%) were owner-occupied, and 34 (11.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0647724|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715031559/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0647724|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Millville CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Millville had a population of 727. The population density was {{convert|88.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Millville was 673 (92.6%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 6 (0.8%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 6 (0.8%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 1 (0.1%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 22 (3.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 19 (2.6%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 50 persons (6.9%).

The Census reported that 727 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 268 households, out of which 95 (35.4%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 180 (67.2%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 24 (9.0%) had a female householder with no husband present, 11 (4.1%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 8 (3.0%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 3 (1.1%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 44 households (16.4%) were made up of individuals, and 24 (9.0%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.71.  There were 215 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (80.2% of all households); the average family size was 3.05.

The population was spread out, with 178 people (24.5%) under the age of 18, 42 people (5.8%) aged 18 to 24, 126 people (17.3%) aged 25 to 44, 246 people (33.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 135 people (18.6%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 47.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.9 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.0 males.

There were 287 housing units at an average density of {{convert|34.9|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 230 (85.8%) were owner-occupied, and 38 (14.2%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 1.7%; the rental vacancy rate was 5.0%.  623 people (85.7% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 104 people (14.3%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, the median income for a household in the CDP was $51,406, and the median income for a family was $53,000. Males had a median income of $41,917 versus $27,031 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $27,218.  About 5.9% of families and 7.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 12.1% of those under age 18 and 2.7% of those age 65 or over.

